entries.name: !=(obj)
entries.desc: Returns true if two objects are not considered of equal value.

entries.name: ==(obj)
entries.desc: Returns true if two objects are considered of equal value.

entries.name: __getobj__()
entries.desc: This method must be overridden by subclasses and should return the object method calls are being delegated to.

entries.name: __setobj__(obj)
entries.desc: This method must be overridden by subclasses and change the object delegate to obj.

entries.name: eql?(obj)
entries.desc: Returns true if two objects are considered of equal value.

entries.name: freeze()
entries.desc: :method: freeze Freeze both the object returned by _getobj_ and self.

entries.name: marshal_dump()
entries.desc: Serialization support for the object returned by _getobj_.

entries.name: marshal_load(data)
entries.desc: Reinitializes delegation from a serialized object.

entries.name: methods(all=true)
entries.desc: Returns the methods available to this delegate object as the union of this object's and _getobj_ methods.

entries.name: protected_methods(all=true)
entries.desc: Returns the methods available to this delegate object as the union of this object's and _getobj_ protected methods.

entries.name: public_methods(all=true)
entries.desc: Returns the methods available to this delegate object as the union of this object's and _getobj_ public methods.
